  "text": "T is part of Genomic Encyclopedia of Type Strains, Phase I: the one thousand microbial genomes project [CITATION_1] which aims in increasing the sequencing coverage of key reference microbial genomes [CITATION_2] . The genome project is deposited in the Genomes OnLine Database [CITATION_3] and the permanent draft genome sequence is deposited in GenBank. Sequencing, finishing and Figure 1 Phylogenetic tree highlighting the position of Brachymonas chironomi relative to the type strains of the other species within the family Comamonadaceae. The sequence alignments were performed by using the CLUSTAL W program and the tree was generated using the maximum likelihood method in MEGA 5 software. Bootstrap values (from 1,000 replicates) greater than 50% are shown at the branch points. The bar indicates a 1% sequence divergence.",
